E^{partial}\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)=uTK_{l}^{exp}\cdot\Phi\left(\frac{log\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)-log\left(uTK_{l}^{exp}\right)+\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2}-\sigma^{2}}{\sigma}\right)\label{eq:PartExp}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally,
 the conditional expectation of 
\begin_inset Formula $UTK_{l}$
\end_inset

 with respect to an upper threshold 
\begin_inset Formula $uTK^{marg}{}_{l}$
\end_inset

 is the fraction between the partial expectation and the cumulative distribution,
 i.e.:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\begin{array}{ccc}
E^{conditional}\left(uTK^{marg}{}_{l}\right) & = & E[UTK_{l}|utk_{l}^{i}\leq uTK^{marg}{}_{l}]\\
 & = & \frac{E^{partial}\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)}{cdf\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)}\\
 & = & \frac{\Phi\left(\frac{log\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)-log\left(uTK_{l}^{exp}\right)+\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2}-\sigma^{2}}{\sigma}\right)}{\Phi\left(\frac{log\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)-log\left(uTK_{l}^{exp}\right)+\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2}}{\sigma}\right)}
\end{array}\label{eq:CondExp}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the practical implementation of the model,
 the conditional expectation has been prone to lead to 'division by zero' errors in GAMS.
 To avoid this,
 we only calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $uTK_{l}$
\end_inset

 after the model is solved in the reporting section of the model.
 
\begin_inset Formula $uTK_{l}$
\end_inset

 only enters in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "qESK"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 By inserting from equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:sqT"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 into equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "qESK"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 we can avoid an explicit representation of 
\begin_inset Formula $uTK_{l}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
qESK=qES\cdot\sum_{l}sqT_{l}^{potential}\cdot cdf\left(uTK^{marg}{}_{l}\right)\cdot\frac{E^{partial}\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)}{cdf\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
which simplifies to
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
qESK=qES\cdot\sum_{l}sqT_{l}^{potential}\cdot E^{partial}\left(uTK_{l}^{marg}\right)\label{eq:qESKalt}
\end{equation}

